13 July 2002|accessdate=22 July 2012}}</ref>||1999, 2000, 2001||2002\n|}\n<small><sup>1</sup>Clyde shared the trophy with [[Third Lanark F.C.|Third Lanark]] in 1952 and with [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in 1961.</small>\n\n===Reserves===\n[[Image:Clyde reserves.JPG|thumb|Clyde lift the Reserve League Cup in May 2008]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:#ffffff; colour:#000000;\"|Honour\n! style=\"background:#ffffff; colour:#000000;\"|Winners\n! style=\"background:#ffffff; colour:#000000;\"|Runners-up\n|-\n|Scottish Reserve League||||1914\n|-\n|Scottish Reserve League West||1988||\n|-\n|[[Scottish Football Alliance]]||||1920, 1957\n|-\n|[[Combined Reserve Football League|Combined Reserve League]]||1962||\n|-\n|Scottish Second XI Cup'''<ref>[http://scottish-football-historical-archive.com/scottishsecondxicup.htm Scottish 2nd XI Cup] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120930025503/http://scottish-football-historical-archive.com/scottishsecondxicup.htm |date=30 September 2012 }}</ref>||1914, 1915, 1942||1897, 1938, 1939, 1946\n|-\n|Reserve League Cup||2008||\n|-\n|Glasgow Second XI Cup||1898||1913\n|-\n|North Eastern Second XI Cup||1892||\n|}\n\n===Youth===\n*League Cup (under 17s):\n**Runners-up: 2004<ref>{{cite news|title=Sore Defeat For Hillcoat's Men|url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2004/05/18/970/|publisher=clydefc.co.uk|date=18 May 2004|accessdate=27 August 2012}}</ref>\n*Rangers Youth Invitational Tournament (under 13s):\n**Winners: 2008<ref>{{cite news|title=Silverware for Community Side|url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2008/07/20/2802/|publisher=clydefc.co.uk|date=20 July 2008|accessdate=27 August 2012}}</ref>\n*Helensburgh Bi-Centennial Tournament (under 13s):\n**Winners: 2002<ref>{{cite news|title=Clyde Under 13's Capture Cup|url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2002/06/08/150/|publisher=clydefc.co.uk|date=8 June 2002|accessdate=28 August 2012}}</ref>\n*Kildrum United Football Festival (under 13s):\n**Winners: 2007<ref>{{cite news|title=Success For Community Teams|url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2007/06/16/2101/|publisher=clydefc.co.uk|date=16 June 2007|accessdate=27 August 2012}}</ref>\n*Oban Saints Youth Tournament (under 13s):\n**Runners-up: 2011<ref>{{cite news|title=Youngsters Excel in Oban|url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2011/06/19/3899/|publisher=clydefc.co.uk|date=19 June 2011|accessdate=27 August 2012}}</ref>\n*CKSSDA 11-a-side Tournament (under 12s):\n**Winners: 2008<ref>{{cite news|title=Success for Clyde Youngsters|url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2008/05/19/2730/|publisher=clydefc.co.uk|date=19 May 2008|accessdate=27 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Records==\n\n*'''Record home [[Scottish football attendance records|attendance]]:''' 52,000 vs [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] (28 November 1908) (at [[Shawfield Stadium]]); 8,000 vs [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] ([[Scottish Cup]]) (8 January 2006) (at [[Broadwood Stadium]])\n*'''Record win:''' 11\u20131 vs [[Cowdenbeath F.C.|Cowdenbeath]] (6 October 1951), 10\u20130 vs [[Stranraer F.C.|Stranraer]] (14 August 1957)<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.londonhearts.com/scores/a1950/19570814.html|title = Games Played on Wed 14 Aug 1957|publisher = londonhearts.com|accessdate = 23 July 2012}}</ref>\n*'''Record European win:''' 4\u20130 vs [[RC Lens]] (7 August 1960)\n*'''Record loss:''' 11\u20130 vs [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]] (22 November 1897)\n*'''Most capped player:''' [[Tommy Ring]]: 12 ([[Scotland national football team|Scotland]])\n*'''Most international goals:''' [[Tommy Ring]]: 2 ([[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]), [[Archie Robertson (footballer)|Archie Robertson]]: 2 ([[Scotland national football team|Scotland]])\n*'''Most goals in one season:''' [[Billy McPhail]]: 36 ([[1951\u201352 in Scottish football|1951\u201352]]), Basil Keogh: 36 ([[1956\u201357 in Scottish football|1956\u201357]])\n*'''Youngest player:''' [[Connor Stevenson]], aged 16 years and 245 days (against [[Queen of the South F.C.|Queen of the South]] in the [[Scottish First Division]] on 15 April 2009)\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n\n===All-time league appearances===\n''As of 1 July 2018 (League only, includes appearances as substitute):''\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align: centr; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!style=\"width: 2em;\"| !!Name!!style=\"width: 5em;\"|Seasons!!style=\"width: 5em;\"|Appearances\n|-\n|1||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Brian|Ahern|Brian Ahern (footballer)}} || 1971\u201381 <br /> 1983\u201387 || 420\n|-\n|2||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Tommy|McCulloch|Tommy McCulloch (footballer, born 1934)}} || 1957\u201372 || 378\n|-\n|3||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Ross|McFarlane|Ross McFarlane (footballer)}} || 1983\u201395 || 376\n|-\n|4||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Harry|Haddock}} || 1949\u201363 || 365\n|-\n|5||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|John|McHugh|John McHugh (footballer)}} || 1961\u201375 || 358\n|-\n|6||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Keith|Knox}} || 1987\u201397 || 322\n|-\n|7||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Eddie|Anderson|Eddie Anderson (footballer)}} || 1969\u201380 || 296\n|-\n|8||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Archie|Robertson|Archie Robertson (footballer)}} || 1949\u201361 || 293\n|-\n|9||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Tommy|Ring}} || 1950\u201360 || 280\n|-\n|10||style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{sortname|Jim|Burns|Jim Burns (footballer)}} || 1967\u201376 || 270\n|}\n{{col-3}}\n\n===All-time league goalscorers===\n''As of 1 July 2018 (League matches only, includes appearances as substitute):''\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align: centr; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!style=\"width: 2em;\"|\n!Name\n!style=\"width: 5em;\"|Years\n!style=\"width: 5em;\"|Goals\n|-\n|1||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Tommy Ring]] || 1950\u201360 || 124\n|-\n|2||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Archie Robertson (footballer)|Archie Robertson]] || 1949\u201361 || 121\n|-\n|3||style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Billy Boyd (footballer)|Billy Boyd]] || 1930\u201333 || 91\n|