itle=Harry Receives 66\u201367 Souvenir | publisher=Clyde FC | date=1 May 2014 | accessdate=8 May 2015}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Brian Ahern (footballer)|Brian Ahern]] (2015)<ref name=2015POTYA1>{{cite web | url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2015/04/12/4870/#.VUzed_lViko | title=2015 Awards Evening | publisher=Clyde FC | date=12 April 2015 | accessdate=8 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=2015POTYA2>{{cite web | url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2015/04/19/4886/#.VUzefvlViko | title=Martin Named Player of the Year | publisher=Clyde FC | date=19 April 2015 | accessdate=8 May 2015}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Keith Knox]] (2016)\n*{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Tommy Ring]] (2016)\n*{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Neil Hood]] (2017)\n{{col-end}}\n\nThe club launched its official Hall of Fame in 2011, with five inaugural inductees.<ref>{{cite news | title=Clyde FC Hall of Fame | url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2011/09/28/3960/ | publisher=Clyde FC | date=28 September 2011 | accessdate=22 October 2012}}</ref> Three more were inducted in 2012.<ref name=2012HOF4/> The Clyde team of season 1966\u201367 was inducted in 2014.<ref name=2014HOF1/> There was one inducted in 2015.<ref name=2015POTYA1/> There is also a Hall of Fame section on the club website.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.clydefc.co.uk/news/2012/11/22/4240/ | title=New Hall of Fame Section | publisher=Clyde FC | date=22 November 2012 | accessdate=3 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Achievements==\n{{see also|List of Clyde F.C. seasons}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===League===\n*[[List of Scottish football champions|Scottish Division One]] (Level 1)\n**''Third place'': [[1908\u201309 in Scottish football|1908\u201309]], [[1911\u201312 in Scottish football|1911\u201312]], [[1966\u201367 in Scottish football|1966\u201367]]\n*[[Scottish Football League Division Two|Scottish Division Two]] (Level 2)\n**'''Winners''' (5): [[1904\u201305 in Scottish football|1904\u201305]], [[1951\u201352 in Scottish football|1951\u201352]], [[1956\u201357 in Scottish football|1956\u20131957]], [[1961\u201362 in Scottish football|1961\u201362]], [[1972\u201373 in Scottish football|1972\u201373]]\n**''Runners-up'' (4): [[1903\u201304 in Scottish football|1903\u201304]], [[1905\u201306 in Scottish football|1905\u201306]], [[1925\u201326 in Scottish football|1925\u201326]], [[1963\u201364 in Scottish football|1963\u201364]]\n*[[Scottish Football League First Division|SFL First Division]] (Level 2)\n**''Runners-up'': [[2002\u201303 in Scottish football|2002\u201303]], [[2003\u201304 in Scottish football|2003\u201304]]\n*[[Scottish Football League Second Division|SFL Second Division]] (Level 3)\n**'''Winners''' (4): [[1977\u201378 in Scottish football|1977\u201378]], [[1981\u201382 in Scottish football|1981\u201382]], [[1992\u201393 in Scottish football|1992\u201393]], [[1999\u20132000 in Scottish football|1999\u20132000]]\n*[[Scottish League Two|SPFL League Two]] (Level 4)\n**''Runners-up/Play-off Winners'': [[2018\u201319 in Scottish football|2018\u201319]]\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Cup===\n*[[Scottish Cup]]\n**'''Winners''': [[1938\u201339 Scottish Cup|1938\u201339]], [[1954\u201355 Scottish Cup|1954\u201355]], [[1957\u201358 Scottish Cup|1957\u201358]]\n**''Runners-up'': [[1909\u201310 Scottish Cup|1909\u201310]], [[1911\u201312 Scottish Cup|1911\u201312]], [[1948\u201349 Scottish Cup|1948\u201349]]\n*'[[Scottish Challenge Cup]]\n**Runners-up: [[2006 Scottish Challenge Cup Final|2006\u201307]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Minor trophies===\n[[Image:ClydeEKCup.JPG|thumb|Clyde lift the Tommy McGrane Trophy in 2006]] \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:#ffffff; colour:#000000;\"|Honour\n! style=\"background:#ffffff; colour:#000000;\"|Winners\n! style=\"background:#ffffff; colour:#000000;\"|Runners-up\n|-\n|[[Anglo-Franco-British Friendship Cup|Anglo-French Friendship Cup]]||[[Anglo-Franco-British Friendship Cup#1960-61|1961]]||\n|-\n|[[Southern Football League (Scotland)|Southern League]]||||[[Southern Football League (Scotland) 1940\u201341|1